One of the World’s oldest people, Fredie Blom, has died. He died at the impressive age of 116-years due to natural causes in Cape town.#eNCA spoke to Delft Senior Forum chairperson Ghadija JOHANNESBURG - One of the world’s oldest men, Fredie Blom, has died. He died at the impressive age of 116-years due to natural causes in Cape town. READ: One of world's oldest men marks 116th birthday in SA Delft Senior Forum chairperson, Ghadija Francis, says Oom Fredie will be remembered for the impact he had on the youth. "He was a very humble person, very gentle and he always liked to talk to the youth and he was very loyal to his wife and his children," said Francis. Francis said the community is making plans to honour Fredie's memory.